{[%evp 0,94,17,10,10,-4,-4,-4,7,-5,-7,-7,26,13,8,10,10,7,3,-8,0,-2,27,-15,-11,-11,25,-37,0,-5,-4,-13,-25,-22,-7,-89,-33,-151,-28,-33,-34,-34,-28,-49,-33,-56,-64,-65,-57,-98,-79,-115,-85,-91,-120,-117,-132,-144,-143,-122,-153,-185,-203,-222,-131,-174,-170,-189,-193,-192,-200,-218,-193,-200,-193,-214,-234,-241,-232,-247,-205,-230,-252,-250,-242,-239,-255,-255,-277,-288,-296,-567,-487,-551,-587,-611,-584]} 1. Nf3 d5 2. g3 Nc6 3. d4 Bf5 4. c4 e6 5. Bg2 Nb4 6. Na3 h6 {[%cal Gf5h7,Rf3h4] Useful move against the Nh4 idea, but here it's not the best.} (6... Be7 {is slightly more precise, in my opinion. We prevent Nh4, and maybe we will play h6 later, or maybe not, according to the situation.}) 7. O-O c6 8. Qb3 {[%cal Yc1d2,Yc4c5,Yd2b4] White's plan is clear: Bd2-c5-Bxb4.} Nf6 9. Bd2 a5 10. Ne5 (10. c5 {was critical, and here Black can play} b6 $1 11. Rfc1 {Is a better move.} (11. Bxb4 $6 axb4 12. Qxb4 bxc5 13. dxc5 Qb8 $1 $15 {Black doesn't only have compensation, but also the initiative.}) 11... Be7 12. Bxb4 axb4 13. Qxb4 bxc5 14. dxc5 O-O $44 {Good compensation for Black, but no advantage.}) 10... Nd7 (10... Bd6 $1 11. c5 Bxe5 12. dxe5 Nd7 $15) 11. Nxd7 Qxd7 12. c5 b6 $2 {[%csl Rf8] as we have seen, b6 is the typical idea for Black against this White's approach, but here it's dangerous because we still miss some moves to castle.} (12... Be7 {Had to be played.} 13. Bxb4 axb4 14. Qxb4 O-O $44) 13. Bxb4 $6 (13. cxb6 $1 Be7 14. Rfc1 O-O 15. Nb1 a4 16. Qd1 Qb7 17. a3 Na6 18. Nc3 Qxb6 19. e3 $14) 13... axb4 14. Qxb4 bxc5 15. dxc5 Be7 $44 {[%csl Ra2,Rb2,Rc5] Black always has fantastic compensation in this structure.} 16. e4 Bh7 17. exd5 $6 (17. Rfd1 $1 $13 {[%cal Ga3c4,Gc4b6] With the idea Nc4-Nb6.}) 17... exd5 18. Qc3 Bf6 19. Qd2 Qb7 $3 {[%csl Ra3] Very nice understanding. The priority is not castle, but to limit White's knight a3.} (19... O-O 20. Nc4 $1 $13) 20. Rae1+ Kf8 21. Re2 g5 $17 {Black has a good positional advantage, and later won the game.} 22. f4 g4 23. f5 Kg7 24. Qf4 h5 25. Rfe1 Qb8 26. Qf2 Qb4 27. Kh1 Rhb8 28. Nc2 Qxb2 29. a3 Qc3 30. Nb4 Rc8 31. Re3 Qb2 32. Qf1 Rxa3 33. Rxa3 Qxa3 34. Nd3 Qa6 35. Rd1 Re8 36. Qf2 Qa4 37. Rf1 Qd4 38. Qc2 Bg5 39. Qb1 Re2 40. Nf4 Bxf4 41. Rxf4 Qb2 42. Qg1 Qe5 43. Bf1 Re4 44. f6+ Kh6 45. Rf2 Re3 46. Bg2 Bd3 47. Qc1 Kg6 0-1

