1. Nf3 d5 2. g3 Nc6 3. d4 Bf5 4. Bg2 Nb4 5. Na3 e6 6. O-O Be7 7. Bf4 Nf6 {objectively it's not a bad move, but it allows White to play his idea:} (7... c6 $5 {[%csl Ra3] Is my recommendation, not allowing Nb5 ideas.}) 8. Nb5 O-O 9. a3 (9. Bxc7 {looks very risky, but it's possible:} Qd7 10. c4 $1 {Both sides have to find now a lot of only moves:} dxc4 11. a4 $1 Bc2 $1 12. Ne5 $1 Bxd1 13. Nxd7 Bxe2 14. Nxf8 Bxf1 15. Kxf1 Rxf8 16. Bxb7 Nfd5 $1 $11 {The engine thinks that it's equal.}) 9... Na6 10. c4 {[%csl Ra6] Suddenly, we have a misplaced knight on a6, while White's knight will go on c3. For the engine, that's not a problem, but for a human, it's not something to welcome.} dxc4 (10... c6 11. Nc3 {Equal for the engine, but everybody would take White I guess.}) 11. Ne5 Be4 $1 {important move.} 12. Bxe4 Nxe4 13. Nxc4 Qd5 14. Qb3 Bg5 {Concrete move, it forces White to find best moves, but objectively it's not the best.} (14... c6 $1 15. Nc3 Nxc3 16. Qxc3 (16. bxc3 b5 $1 $11) 16... Rfd8 {Engine shows +0,20, and in a game I would think that Black is almost OK, but few other accurate moves will be required.}) 15. Bxg5 Nxg5 16. f3 $6 {dubious decision:} (16. h4 $1 Ne4 17. Rad1 $14 {[%cal Gb5c3] Nc3 next, and it looks unpleasant.}) 16... c6 $1 17. Nc3 Qxd4+ 18. e3 Qc5 $15 {Black is already better, objectively. Still, a game is a game, and after some mistakes from both sides, White managed to win, but this goes beyond the purpose of this course.} 1-0

