{[#]} {[%tqu "En","Critical position. Black to move.","","","g4h3","Fantastic move. What is our idea? That our bishop is very safe on h3, and White cannot win any important tempo against it. Second idea is that we prevent White's 00.",10,"e7h4","has been often tried by Black. It's not so bad, but the engine thinks that White is slightly better.",0,"g8f6","looks like a human move, but after",0]} 11... Bh3 $1 {Fantastic move. What is our idea? That our bishop is very safe on h3, and White cannot win any important tempo against it. Second idea is that we prevent White's 00.} (11... Bxh4 {has been often tried by Black. It's not so bad, but the engine thinks that White is slightly better.} 12. gxh4 Nge7 13. Rg1 $1 Bf5 14. Bf3 O-O 15. h5 $1 $14 {Very important move: All White's counterplay is connected with the h6 idea.}) (11... Nf6 {looks like a human move, but after} 12. Bg2 $1 {[%csl Gh3][%cal Rg4h3,Gg2h3] White takes control of the important h3 square.} O-O 13. O-O $14 {[%csl Rg4] White is slightly better, especially because he can wait the best moment to win the pair of bishops.}) 12. Ng2 Nf6 13. Bf3 Bg4 $1 $11 {We finally manage to exchange the light squares bishop. Yes, our bishop lost some tempi, but also White's knight on g2 did so!} *

